title: Tiffany Hartwell Memorial Window Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from (attributed to) Agnes F. Northrop and Tiffany Studios’, Hartwell Memorial Window, 1917, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The Hartwell Memorial Window, 1917 is one of the most extraordinary leaded glass windows ever made by Tiffany Studios, the leading glass firm of America’s Gilded Age.   Attributed to Tiffany’s foremost landscape window designer, Agnes Northrop, the Hartwell Memorial Window stands 23 feet high by 16 feet wide. Made up of 48 separate panels, it is a technical marvel in the medium of glass and a work of stunning beauty.
